                <div class="col-text">
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Determining Logical Scope:</strong> Early feedback indicated that users found it difficult to determine the appropriate location for automation logic that applied across multiple case types.</li>
                        <li><strong>Card Sort Results:</strong> Conducted a card sorting activity with seven participants, showing that users naturally group automation needs by **scope (Global vs. Local)** rather than trigger or action.</li>
                        <li><strong>Precedence Rules:</strong> Designed a hierarchical inheritance model. Conflict resolution executes from the highest level down to the lowest—specific rules (local) always take priority over general rules (global).</li>
                        <li><strong>Consistency:</strong> This logic matches the existing "lowest level wins" pattern for user-defined data fields and forms, keeping the system logic consistent.</li>
                    </ul>
